---
import InnerLayout from '../layouts/InnerLayout.astro';
const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Organization",
  "name": "AnyInterview",
  "url": "https://anyinterview.to",
  "description": "AI-powered structured interview platform",
  "foundingDate": "2025",
  "contactPoint": {"@type":"ContactPoint","email":"hello@anyinterview.to","contactType":"customer support"}
};
---
<InnerLayout title="About AnyInterview — Why We Built This" description="AnyInterview is built for organizations who conduct structured interviews at scale. Meet the team and learn why we built this." schema={schema} canonical="https://anyinterview.to/about">

  <section class="ip-hero">
    <div class="ip-hero-inner">
      <span class="ip-eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>We built the interview <em>we always needed.</em></h1>
      <p class="ip-hero-sub">AnyInterview started as a question: why does every structured interview require a human to be in the room? The answer turned out to be: it doesn't.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-section">
    <div class="ip-section-inner ip-section-inner--narrow">
      <div class="ip-prose">
        <p>There's a strange asymmetry at the core of modern knowledge work. Organizations need to interview thousands of people — candidates, customers, research participants, employees, audit subjects. But the humans doing the interviewing have twenty-four hours in a day and a calendar that's already full.</p>
        <p>The bottleneck isn't judgment. It's time. When interviews don't happen, decisions get made on less information. Candidates ghost. Customers churn without a word. Research velocity drops. Audits get thin. The interview is the data collection mechanism for some of the most consequential decisions organizations make — and it almost never scales.</p>
        <p>We built AnyInterview to solve that. A structured conversation, configured in chat, conducted by AI in your voice — and returned to you as a complete record. The interview happens. The data lands. The calendar stays free.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-section ip-section--alt">
    <div class="ip-section-inner">
      <span class="ip-section-label">What we believe</span>
      <h2>Built on a few <em>hard-won beliefs.</em></h2>
      <div class="ip-card-grid ip-card-grid--2">

        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <line x1="12" y1="2" x2="12" y2="6"/><line x1="12" y1="18" x2="12" y2="22"/>
              <line x1="4.93" y1="4.93" x2="7.76" y2="7.76"/><line x1="16.24" y1="16.24" x2="19.07" y2="19.07"/>
              <line x1="2" y1="12" x2="6" y2="12"/><line x1="18" y1="12" x2="22" y2="12"/>
              <line x1="4.93" y1="19.07" x2="7.76" y2="16.24"/><line x1="16.24" y1="7.76" x2="19.07" y2="4.93"/>
              <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Structured conversations produce better decisions</h3>
          <p>An unstructured interview is a conversation. A structured interview is a measurement. The quality of your process determines the quality of your signal.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <polygon points="13 2 3 14 12 14 11 22 21 10 12 10 13 2"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Speed shouldn't mean less rigor</h3>
          <p>The tradeoff between 'fast' and 'thorough' is mostly artificial. The right tools make it disappear.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <ellipse cx="12" cy="5" rx="9" ry="3"/><path d="M21 12c0 1.66-4 3-9 3s-9-1.34-9-3"/>
              <path d="M3 5v14c0 1.66 4 3 9 3s9-1.34 9-3V5"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>The interview is a data problem</h3>
          <p>Transcripts, scores, recordings, timestamps — every interview is a dataset waiting to be used. We built for that from day one.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="ip-card">
          <div class="ip-card-icon">
            <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
              <path d="M12 22s8-4 8-10V5l-8-3-8 3v7c0 6 8 10 8 10z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <h3>Trust requires a paper trail</h3>
          <p>Consent, encryption, audit playback. If you can't show your work, you didn't do the work.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-section">
    <div class="ip-section-inner ip-section-inner--narrow">
      <div class="ip-prose">
        <h2>The team</h2>
        <p>We're a small team. Most of us came from recruiting, research, or building AI systems. We've been on both sides of the interview table more times than we can count.</p>
        <p>We build in public, ship every week, and respond to every message personally. If you use AnyInterview, you can reach us directly.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-section ip-section--alt">
    <div class="ip-section-inner ip-section-inner--narrow">
      <div class="ip-prose">
        <h2>Built in public</h2>
        <p>We publish our changelog weekly. We share what we're working on. We respond to feature requests within a day. When something breaks, we say so.</p>
        <p>We think the way you build a product says something about what you believe. We believe in showing our work.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="ip-closing">
    <div class="ip-closing-inner">
      <h2>Come see what <em>we're building.</em></h2>
      <p>Book a demo — we'll show you the product and tell you what's coming.</p>
      <a href="#" class="ip-cta-primary" data-action="open-demo">Book a Demo →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</InnerLayout>
